    },
    {
      "para_id": "p48",
      "section_id": "s14",
      "section_path": [
        "8. Urgent Measures for Digital Fairness",
        "Conclusion and Key Takeaways"
      ],
      "ordinal": 48,
      "text": "Key priorities include improving transparency, protecting vulnerable groups, and supporting SMEs in compliance efforts. Respondents emphasize that consumer education and empowerment are essential for the Act’s success, alongside practical measures that ensure fair competition and responsible digital practices. We recommend considering the possibility of using self regulatory institutions, such as EASA, which have already proven to be effective in other areas (e.g., influencer marketing), as all the parts of the supply chain are equally represented.",
      "char_len": 554,
      "chunk_word_count": 77,
      "ratios": {
